Class OutputOperator

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.netbeans.jemmy.Outputable, org.netbeans.jemmy.Timeoutable

    public class OutputOperator
extends TopComponentOperator
    Provides access to the Output window and it's subcomponents. Output window might contain one or more output tabs. It is better to use OutputTabOperator if you want to work with a particular output tab.

    Usage:

          OutputOperator oo = new OutputOperator();
      System.out.println("TEXT from active output tab="+oo.getText().substring(0, 10));
      // get OutputTabOperator instance
      OutputTabOperator oto = oo.getOutputTab("myoutput");
      // or
      // OutputTabOperator oto = new OutputTabOperator("myoutput");
      // call an action from context menu
      oo.find();
      // close output
      oo.close();
    See Also:
    OutputTabOperator
